Package com.iopipe

This package contians the classes and interfaces which are used to interact with the IOpipe service.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IOpipeConstants
    This class contains constants which are used by the service.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CustomMetric
    This represents a custom metric which may have a string or long value, these may be used to add extra data points that are normally not present.
    IOpipeConfiguration
    This class contains the configuration for IOpipe and specifies the settings which are to be used when the server is contacted.
    IOpipeConfigurationBuilder
    This class is used to initialize instances of IOpipeConfiguration This class is not thread safe.
    IOpipeExecution
    This class provides access to information and functionality which is specific to a single execution of a method.
    IOpipeMeasurement
    This class is used to keep track of measurements during execution.
    IOpipeService
    This class provides a single connection to the IOpipe service which may then be used to send multiple requests to as methods are ran.
    PerformanceEntry
    This class represents a single performance entry which is used to record the start time and the potential duration of an event.
    SimpleRequestHandlerWrapper<I,O>
    This class is used as a base to create simple instances of wrapped lambdas which will provide measurements to the IOpipe service.
    SimpleRequestStreamHandlerWrapper
    This class is used as a base to create simple instances of wrapped lambdas which will provide measurements to the IOpipe service.
    SystemMeasurement
    This class reads and provides a snapshot of all the system information which is needed to keep track of measurements.
    SystemMeasurement.Cpu
    Contains information about a single CPU.
    SystemMeasurement.Times
    This contains the process time information.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IOpipeTimeOutException
    This is used when a request being executed has timed out.

Package com.iopipe Description

This package contians the classes and interfaces which are used to interact with the IOpipe service.
